01:22:43,713 --> 01:22:44,756
Thanks.

1333
01:22:55,809 --> 01:22:58,137
Wah. Thanks, man.

1334
01:22:58,171 --> 01:22:59,631
SUSAN: Excellent.

1335
01:23:06,826 --> 01:23:09,711
You're a real magician, Richard.

1336
01:23:10,511 --> 01:23:11,762
Thank you.

1337
01:23:14,786 --> 01:23:16,315
Merry Christmas.

1338
01:23:20,555 --> 01:23:21,772
Thank you.

1339
01:23:22,362 --> 01:23:23,509
Wow.

1340
01:23:26,047 --> 01:23:27,820
Merry Christmas to you.

1341
01:23:29,140 --> 01:23:31,851
Hey, let's go.

1342
01:23:34,423 --> 01:23:35,883
You can open it later.

1343
01:23:36,787 --> 01:23:38,351
Celia, I...

1344
01:23:38,386 --> 01:23:39,671
You have to go.

1345
01:23:39,741 --> 01:23:40,923
Yeah.

1346
01:23:42,313 --> 01:23:43,356
Good luck.

1347
01:23:43,738 --> 01:23:45,093
You, too.

1348
01:24:08,763 --> 01:24:12,899
GUS: I couldn't bother you for something to nibble on for the road?

1349
01:24:31,217 --> 01:24:32,468
Richard.

1350
01:24:32,502 --> 01:24:34,171
What are you wearing?

1351
01:24:35,456 --> 01:24:38,758
And you, you changed your hair?

1352
01:24:39,836 --> 01:24:41,018
One side is

1353
01:24:41,991 --> 01:24:43,312
bluish.

1354
01:24:43,346 --> 01:24:45,189
I was probably sleeping on the other.

1355
01:24:45,223 --> 01:24:46,961
-What? -Nothing.

1356
01:24:46,961 --> 01:24:49,186
Oh. Well, I'm glad you're here.

1357
01:24:51,375 --> 01:24:53,912
Oh, thank you. For me?

1358
01:24:54,538 --> 01:24:56,242
Actually, that's for me.

1359
01:24:56,659 --> 01:24:57,701
Oh.

1360
01:24:58,014 --> 01:24:59,300
Cute.

1361
01:24:59,334 --> 01:25:01,385
Everybody's at the table already.

1362
01:25:09,553 --> 01:25:12,125
GEORGE: We're, we're very lucky that Richard's here.

1363
01:25:13,724 --> 01:25:15,253
He's afraid of flying.

1364
01:25:16,087 --> 01:25:18,173
I'm afraid to fly, too.

1365
01:25:20,293 --> 01:25:24,499
Richard's been studying up on everything there is to know about Yamashitsu.

1366
01:25:26,063 --> 01:25:27,244
Haven't you, Richard?

1367
01:25:27,662 --> 01:25:28,704
Yeah.

1368
01:25:30,130 --> 01:25:31,624
I think it's time.

1369
01:25:32,145 --> 01:25:33,258
For what?

1370
01:25:33,292 --> 01:25:34,578
Our announcement.

1371
01:25:34,613 --> 01:25:36,073
You have the ring, right?

1372
01:25:36,837 --> 01:25:38,367
(CLEARS THROAT) Everyone.

1373
01:25:40,244 --> 01:25:42,572
Richard has something he'd like to say.

1374
01:25:44,692 --> 01:25:46,152
Uh.

1375
01:25:46,396 --> 01:25:47,439
Yeah.

1376
01:25:48,898 --> 01:25:50,567
I wanna show you all something.

1377
01:26:15,905 --> 01:26:17,712
Would you please excuse me?

1378
01:26:19,693 --> 01:26:23,689
Larry, some more sake for our Japanese friends.

1379
01:26:25,775 --> 01:26:28,000
Why are you doing stupid tricks?

1380
01:26:28,034 --> 01:26:29,877
This is supposed to be special, Richard.

1381
01:26:29,911 --> 01:26:31,858
It's our first Christmas together.

1382
01:26:31,892 --> 01:26:34,117
This isn't Christmas.

1383
01:26:34,152 --> 01:26:35,612
This is a Board meeting.

1384
01:26:35,646 --> 01:26:37,593
Why didn't you make the announcement?

1385
01:26:40,060 --> 01:26:41,103
Sara,

1386
01:26:42,598 --> 01:26:44,092
I can't marry you.

1387
01:26:45,518 --> 01:26:46,769
What?

1388
01:26:46,803 --> 01:26:48,610
Richard, I've been planning this.

1389
01:26:48,646 --> 01:26:50,036
Sara.

1390
01:26:50,523 --> 01:26:51,808
Sara, please.

1391
01:26:51,808 --> 01:26:54,658
This would be a mistake for both of us.

1392
01:26:54,693 --> 01:26:56,813
A big mistake.

1393
01:26:56,848 --> 01:27:00,393
I fell in love with you for all the wrong reasons.

1394
01:27:00,428 --> 01:27:02,826
I know this because...

1395
01:27:07,032 --> 01:27:13,149
I know this because I've fallen in love with someone for no reason at all.

1396
01:27:15,548 --> 01:27:16,590
I'm sorry.

1397
01:27:18,640 --> 01:27:19,823
What are you doing?

1398
01:27:19,857 --> 01:27:22,117
Get back to the table, both of you.

1399
01:27:22,151 --> 01:27:23,681
It's Christmas, for Christ's sake.

1400
01:27:23,715 --> 01:27:25,939
Richard just told me that he won't marry me.

1401
01:27:25,975 --> 01:27:27,017
What?

1402
01:27:27,052 --> 01:27:28,616
He's in love with someone else.

1403
01:27:31,570 --> 01:27:32,787
Where are you going?

1404
01:27:34,177 --> 01:27:35,741
You can't leave.

1405
01:27:35,776 --> 01:27:37,166
We haven't made the merger.

1406
01:27:37,166 --> 01:27:39,390
We didn't come here for business.

1407
01:27:39,426 --> 01:27:41,337
We came for Christmas.

1408
01:27:45,021 --> 01:27:46,203
But...

1409
01:27:48,949 --> 01:27:52,494
Gentlemen, come on. We can cut a deal here.

1410
01:27:52,564 --> 01:27:54,684
This merger's a natural.

1411
01:27:54,718 --> 01:27:58,889
Billings and Yamashitsu. Or, Yamashitsu and Billings, it doesn't matter.

1412
01:27:58,924 --> 01:28:00,627
It's a marriage made in heaven.

1413
01:28:00,661 --> 01:28:02,365
-Come on, gentlemen. -(HUMMING)

1414
01:28:02,434 --> 01:28:04,415
GEORGE: Here, here's what we'll do. If you want...

1415
01:28:06,327 --> 01:28:09,039
I can't remember the last time I had sushi.

1416
01:28:09,073 --> 01:28:10,741
Care to join me?

1417
01:28:10,811 --> 01:28:12,201
Where you headed, Gus?

1418
01:28:12,931 --> 01:28:15,329
Anywhere the customer wants.

1419
01:28:15,364 --> 01:28:17,032
Don't have any money.

1420
01:28:17,102 --> 01:28:18,145
Hey.

1421
01:28:20,369 --> 01:28:21,760
It's Christmas.

1422
01:28:22,489 --> 01:28:24,158
Yes, it is, Gus.

1423
01:28:24,539 --> 01:28:25,791
Yes, it is.

1424
01:28:26,556 --> 01:28:27,980
Hallelujah.

1425
01:28:30,657 --> 01:28:32,117
(CAR STARTS)

1426
01:28:34,168 --> 01:28:35,940
GEORGE: Oh, God.

1427
01:28:35,975 --> 01:28:37,261
(CUCKOO CLOCK CHIMES)

1428
01:28:46,402 --> 01:28:48,800
(MUMBLES)

1429
01:28:54,778 --> 01:28:55,821
UNCLE HENRICK: Yes, yes.

1430
01:28:55,856 --> 01:28:57,489
What a good idea.

1431
01:29:00,826 --> 01:29:05,831
Oh, Celia, we're all going on vacation, to Las Vegas.

1432
01:29:07,569 --> 01:29:09,063
I'm going to Paris.

1433
01:29:11,393 --> 01:29:12,435
Dad,

1434
01:29:14,277 --> 01:29:16,919
I've wanted this since I was a baby.

1435
01:29:18,066 --> 01:29:19,526
I've dreamed about it.

1436
01:29:21,541 --> 01:29:23,418
Please give me your blessing.

1437
01:29:38,676 --> 01:29:40,727
(MUMBLES)

1438
01:29:53,865 --> 01:29:55,846
I love you.

1439
01:29:55,881 --> 01:29:57,063
(GRUNTS)

1440
01:29:58,140 --> 01:29:59,183
Pleasure.

1441
01:30:00,226 --> 01:30:01,268
Bye.

1442
01:30:02,728 --> 01:30:04,571
Bye, Mom. Bye, Dad.

1443
01:30:09,019 --> 01:30:10,444
I love you all!

1444
01:30:10,479 --> 01:30:13,260
-We love you. -Love you, too.

1445
01:30:13,329 --> 01:30:14,719
-DENNIS: See you, kid. -MOM: Bon voyage.

1446
01:30:26,015 --> 01:30:27,823
DENNIS: Bye, sis.

1447
01:30:27,858 --> 01:30:29,109
UNCLE HENRICK: Goodbye.

1448
01:30:30,603 --> 01:30:31,716
Take care.

1449
01:30:33,350 --> 01:30:36,721
RICHARD AND GUS: # Four calling cards Three French hens

1450
01:30:36,721 --> 01:30:38,355
# Two turtle gloves

1451
01:30:38,389 --> 01:30:44,228
# And a cartilage in my left knee #

1452
01:30:44,263 --> 01:30:48,503
Oh, oh, boy. Am I glad you guys came along.

1453
01:30:49,754 --> 01:30:51,249
I'm stuck.

1454
01:30:51,249 --> 01:30:52,291
I need a lift.

1455
01:30:53,751 --> 01:30:59,834
Gee, I think I saw a call box about ten miles down the road.

1456
01:30:59,834 --> 01:31:04,144
Look, Richie, I liked your damn tricks, okay?

1457
01:31:04,178 --> 01:31:06,055
Dogs do tricks, Billy.

1458
01:31:06,959 --> 01:31:08,766
I do magic.

1459
01:31:19,263 --> 01:31:21,870
RICHARD AND GUS: (CONTINUE SINGING)

1460
01:31:26,562 --> 01:31:31,706
# ...Gathering winter fuel #

1461
01:31:36,433 --> 01:31:38,658
-Thanks, Gus. -Merry Christmas.

1462
01:31:38,727 --> 01:31:40,013
Same to you.

1463
01:31:42,064 --> 01:31:43,801
What are you doing back?

1464
01:31:43,837 --> 01:31:45,296
Where's Celia?

1465
01:31:46,026 --> 01:31:47,486
Ah.

1466
01:31:47,486 --> 01:31:50,440
She went into town to catch the last bus to the city.

1467
01:31:50,510 --> 01:31:52,317
She's on her way to Paris, Richard.

1468
01:31:52,317 --> 01:31:53,568
What?

1469
01:31:55,862 --> 01:31:57,252
I have to stop her.

1470
01:32:00,520 --> 01:32:01,563
I have an idea.

1471
01:32:03,995 --> 01:32:05,734
(MUMBLES)

1472
01:32:36,979 --> 01:32:39,656
-Bye, Mikey. -Goodbye, Celia.

1473
01:33:39,299 --> 01:33:43,887
Celia!

1474
01:33:44,687 --> 01:33:45,938
Stop the bus.

1475
01:33:57,268 --> 01:33:58,763
(SCREAMS)

1476
01:34:01,787 --> 01:34:03,316
